		<p>Near the beginning of this article it states, &#8220;Dr. Marilyn Huestis of the National Institute on Drug Abuse, a government research lab, says that soon there will be a saliva test to detect recent marijuana use.</p>
<p>But government officials say that doesn’t address the question of impairment.&#8221;</p>
